The Rivers State Government has revealed residents of the state will enjoy free bus service within some part of the state. Governor Nyesom Wike made this announcement in a Twitter post on Thursday. The free bus rides would commence from the 1st of June. According to the governor, the free bus service would only be within some local government areas in the state. Local Government areas that will benefit from the service include Port Harcourt Local Government Area (PHALGA), Obio-Akpor local government area (OBALGA), Oyigbo & Eleme LGAs. The project is aimed at cushioning the constraints of the Covid-19 pandemic on our citizens. Source By Precious Akutamadu Port Harcourt - Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on Friday completed the distribution of sensitive and non-sensitive election materials to all the 23 Local Government Areas of Rivers. The materials were conveyed from the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) Port Harcourt by relevant authorities to the 23… February 22, 2019 In "Politics" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Transportation Minister, Rotimi Amaechi, is a former boss of current Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, and the lawmaker representing Rivers Southeast Senatorial District, Senator Magnus Abe. But today, the three are at loggerheads. Who will have the upper hand this time? Amaechi, an Ikwerre from Ubima… September 23, 2018 In "Top Stories" By Simeon Nwakaudu While many states are wallowing in regrets and numerous inexplicable excuses by their governors,  Rivers State is basking in the euphoria of electing a well groomed and prepared governor.  Nyesom Ezenwo Wike,  just like his promoters pledged, has started the process of planting Rivers State on higher… July 13, 2015 In "Opinion"